\subsection{Method \code{cancel_withdrawal()}}{
Cancel Withdrawal

Cancels a pending withdrawal request. Only withdrawals with \code{PROCESSING}
status can be cancelled. Once a withdrawal has moved to \code{WALLET_PROCESSING}
or later, it cannot be reversed.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated DELETE to the withdrawal-specific endpoint.
\item \strong{Response}: KuCoin returns \code{NULL} data on success.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns a \code{data.table} with the cancelled withdrawal ID.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{DELETE https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/withdrawals/\{withdrawalId\}}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/account-info/withdrawals/cancel-withdrawal}{KuCoin Cancel Withdrawal}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Error Recovery}: Cancel a withdrawal if the destination address was incorrect.
\item \strong{Strategy Change}: Cancel pending withdrawals if market conditions change and funds are needed for trading.
}
}

